MPs raise card surcharge issue in Rajya Sabha 
16-3-2017 
NEW DELHI: Several opposition members raised on Thursday the issue of transaction surcharge on credit/debit card payments for fuel purchase at petrol pumps as well as new charges after a certain number of ATM withdrawals.SP MP Naresh Agrawal said the government had promised a "digital India" and that no fuel surcharge would be levied on payment through credit and debit cards, but customers are still paying them.Following this, deputy chairman P J Kurien asked MoS for parliamentary affairs Mukhtar Abbas Naqvi to convey the concerns to the finance minister. 
